\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b 2. Write the step How to configure server step by step?\par
\b0 Ans. Windows Server 2016 \f1\endash  Initial Configuration Steps\par
\b Sign in & rename the server\b0\par
\f0\lang1033 1. \f1\lang9 GUI: Server Manager \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Local Server \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Computer name \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Change\'85 \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 set name \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Restart.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1. Rename-Computer -NewName "SRV-APP01" -Restart\par
2. Set a static IP & DNS\par
3. GUI: Control Panel \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Network and Sharing Center \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Change adapter settings \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Ethernet \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Properties \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 IPv4.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1. New-NetIPAddress -InterfaceAlias "Ethernet" -IPAddress 192.168.1.10 -PrefixLength 24 -DefaultGateway 192.168.1.1\par
2. Set-DnsClientServerAddress -InterfaceAlias "Ethernet" -ServerAddresses 192.168.1.10,8.8.8.8\par
3. Set time zone & NTP\par
4. GUI: Date & time settings \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Time zone.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1. tzutil /s "India Standard Time"\par
2.w32tm/config/syncfromflags:manual /manualpeerlist:"time.windows.com" /updatew32tm /resync\par
3. Enable Remote Desktop (if needed)\par
4. GUI: Server Manager \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Local Server \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Remote Desktop \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Enable.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1. Set-ItemProperty 'HKLM:\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Terminal Server' -Name "fDenyTSConnections" -Value 0\par
2. Enable-NetFirewallRule -DisplayGroup "Remote Desktop"\par
3. Windows Update & activation\par
4. GUI: Settings \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Update & security \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Check for updates, then System \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 About \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Activate.\par
5. Core servers: run sconfig and choose the Update/Activation options.\par
6. Configure Windows Firewall (profiles/rules)\par
7. GUI: Windows Firewall with Advanced Security.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1. Get-NetFirewallProfile | Set-NetFirewallProfile -Enabled True\par
2. Install required roles & features\par
3. GUI: Server Manager \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Add roles and features.\par
\b PowerShell (examples):\b0\par
1.Install-WindowsFeature AD-Domain-Services, DNS -IncludeManagementTools\par
2. Install-WindowsFeature DHCP -IncludeManagementTools\par
3. Install-WindowsFeature FS-FileServer\par
4. Install-WindowsFeature Web-Server -IncludeManagementTools\par
5. Install-WindowsFeature Windows-Server-Backup\par
6. If this server will be a Domain Controller (AD DS)\par
7. Promote to Domain Controller\par
8. GUI: In Server Manager, after AD DS install \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Promote this server to a domain controller \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 choose:\par
\b PowerShell (new forest example):\par
\b0 1.Install-ADDSForest -DomainName "corp.local" -SafeModeAdministratorPassword (Read-Host -AsSecureString)\par
2. DNS basics\par
3. In DNS Manager, set Forwarders to your ISP/public DNS (e.g., 8.8.8.8).\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1. Add-DnsServerForwarder -IPAddress 8.8.8.8\par
2. Create users & groups\par
3. GUI: Active Directory Users and Computers (dsa.msc).\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1.New-ADUser -Name "Harshita Kumawat" -SamAccountName hkumawat -AccountPassword (Read-Host -AsSecureString) -Enabled $true\par
2.New-ADGroup "App-Admins" -GroupScope Global -Path "CN=Users,DC=corp,DC=local"\par
3. Add-ADGroupMember "App-Admins" hkumawat\par
4. Join member servers/PCs to the domain\par
5. GUI: System Properties \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Change \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Domain: corp.local \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 enter domain creds \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Restart.\par
\b PowerShell (on the member computer):\par
\b0 1. Add-Computer -DomainName corp.local -Restart\par
2. If this server will be DHCP\par
3. Authorize DHCP & create scope\par
4. GUI: DHCP Manager \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Right-click server \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Authorize; then IPv4 \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 New Scope.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
1.Add-DhcpServerInDC -DnsName "srv-dc01.corp.local" -IpAddress 192.168.1.10\par
2. Add-DhcpServerv4Scope -Name "LAN" -StartRange 192.168.1.100 -EndRange 192.168.1.200 -SubnetMask 255.255.255.0\par
3. Set-DhcpServerv4OptionValue -OptionId 3 -Value 192.168.1.1\par
4. Set-DhcpServerv4OptionValue -OptionId 6 -Value 192.168.1.10\par
5. Set-DhcpServerv4OptionValue -OptionId 15 -Value "corp.local"\par
6. If this server will be a File Server\par
7. Create data volume & NTFS permissions\par
8. GUI: Disk Management \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 initialize/format \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 assign drive letter.\par
9. Create folders (e.g., D:\\Shares\\Dept). Set NTFS: Properties \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Security (use groups, not users).\par
10. Create SMB shares\par
11. GUI: Server Manager \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 File and Storage Services \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 Shares \f2\u8594?\f1  \f0 New Share.\par
\b PowerShell:\b0\par
