\b0 Ans. Steps to Upgrade to Windows Server 2016\par
\b 1. Verify Upgrade Path\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf7\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Supported in-place upgrades:\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Windows Server 2012 \f2\u8594?\f0  Windows Server 2016\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Windows Server 2012 R2 \f2\u8594?\f0  Windows Server 2016\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}You cannot upgrade directly from Windows Server 2008/R2 or older. Those require migration or a step-up upgrade.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b 2. Prepare for Upgrade\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf7\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Check system requirements: CPU, RAM, storage (minimum 32 GB).\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Update the existing server with latest patches and service packs.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Check application/role compatibility (some roles may need reinstallation).\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Backup the server (system state + data).\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Disable or temporarily remove third-party antivirus/security software.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b 3. Insert Installation Media\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf7\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Insert the Windows Server 2016 DVD/USB or mount the ISO.\par
