\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj 22. What is Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS), and what are its key components?\lang1033\par
\b0 Ans. \b Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS)\par

\pard{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf7\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b0 A directory service in Windows Server that stores and manages information about users, computers, and resources.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Provides authentication, authorization, and centralized management.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Key Components:\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf7\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Domain \f1\endash\f0  Logical group of objects (users, computers, etc.).\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Tree \f1\endash\f0  Collection of domains in a hierarchy.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Forest \f1\endash\f0  Highest-level container with multiple trees.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Organizational Units (OUs) \f1\endash\f0  Containers to organize objects and apply policies.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Objects \f1\endash\f0  Users, groups, computers, printers.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Schema \f1\endash\f0  Rules/definitions of objects and attributes.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Global Catalog \f1\endash\f0  Searchable index of all objects in a forest.\par
{\pntext\f7\'B7\tab}Domain Controllers (DCs) \f1\endash\f0  Servers that store AD DS and handle authentication.\b\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj 23. How do you create a new Active Directory user account in Windows Server ?\par
